Message.MsgText: ADMG0621E=ADMG0621E: Server type not provided for command {0}. Server type is required when template names are specified.
Message.Explanation: The server type is required for the command.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the server type is specified.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0657E=ADMG0657E: Configuration data {1} specified for command {0} is invalid
Message.Explanation: Invalid configuration data is specified in the command.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the configuration data specified for the command is valid.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0620E=ADMG0620E: Invalid server type {1} passed for command {0}
Message.Explanation: The server type specified is invalid.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that a valid server type is specified.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0656E=ADMG0656E: File name {1} specified for command {0} is invalid. It cannot be created or it does not exist.
Message.Explanation: Invalid file name is specified. The file can not be created or the file does not exist.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the file name specified for the command is valid.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0655E=ADMG0655E: Configuration data {0} specified in properties file {1} is invalid
Message.Explanation: Invalid configuration data is specified in property file.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the configuration data specified in the property file is valid.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0654E=ADMG0654E: Configuration data {0} specified is invalid
Message.Explanation: Invalid configuration data is specified.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the configuration data is valid.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0653E=ADMG0653E: Configuration property {0} specified in section {1} is invalid
Message.Explanation: Invalid configuration property is specified.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the configuration property specified in the section is valid.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0652E=ADMG0652E: User not authorized to delete configuration {0}
Message.Explanation: User does not have the permission to delete WebSphere Application Server configuration.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the user has the permission to delete configuration.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0651E=ADMG0651E: User not authorized to apply configuration {0}
Message.Explanation: User does not have the permission to apply WebSphere Application Server configuration.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the user has the permission to apply configuration.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0650E=ADMG0650E: User not authorized to extract configuration information {0}
Message.Explanation: User does not have the permission to extract WebSphere Application Server configuration information.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that user has the permission to extract configuration information.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0249E=ADMG0249E: The server name {0} is invalid.
Message.Explanation: The server name is invalid. The server can not be created.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a valid server name.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0248E=ADMG0248E: {0} exists within node {1}.
Message.Explanation: The server name has been used already. The server can not be created.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a different server name.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0247E=ADMG0247E: Server Name is required.
Message.Explanation: The server name is required for the command.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the server name is specified.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0029W=ADMG0029W: Server {0} is a cluster member of cluster {1}.
Message.Explanation: A server can not be converted to a server cluster if it is part of an existing cluster.
Message.UserResponse: No user action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0102E=ADMG0102E: Invalid character in new cell name {0}.
Message.Explanation: The cell name cannot have leading or trailing spaces and cannot contain any of the following characters: \ / , # $ @ : ; " * ? < > | = + & % ' [ ]
Message.UserResponse: Specify a different cell name that complies with cell name rules.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0028W=ADMG0028W: The system is unable to delete the server definition for cluster member {0}.
Message.Explanation: The cluster member is removed from a server cluster, but the server definition of the cluster member cannot be removed.
Message.UserResponse: Manually remove the server definition from the cluster configuration.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0101E=ADMG0101E: renameCell command can only run in local mode. Stop the application server or deployment manager before running this command.
Message.Explanation: renameCell command can not be run when administrative client is connected to a running server. This command changes the cell name and hence needs to be run when server is shut down.
Message.UserResponse: Stop the server by running stopServer or stopManager script before running this command.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0809I=ADMG0809I: Attribute type specified in properties file does not match with actual attribute. Section={0} attributeName={1} propertyName={2} propertyType={3} actualPropertyType={4}.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0027E=ADMG0027E: The system is unable to find the ServerEntry value for server {0}.
Message.Explanation: An inconsistency exists between the server configuration and its serverindex.xml document.
Message.UserResponse: Manually edit the server index document to keep it consistent with the server configuration.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0808I=ADMG0808I: Deleting {0}.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0026E=ADMG0026E: The system is unable to find the server definition for cluster member {0} of cluster {1}.
Message.Explanation: When a new cluster member is added to a server cluster, the applications that are deployed on the clusters are automatically deployed on the new cluster member. In this case, the definition of an existing cluster member cannot be found, so the application deployment information cannot be updated correctly for the new cluster member.
Message.UserResponse: Check the server cluster configuration for inconsistencies or errors.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0025W=ADMG0025W: The system is unable to define the SERVER_LOG_ROOT variable map for server {0}:{1}
Message.Explanation: The server was created successfully, but the SERVER_LOG_ROOT variable map creation under the newly created server scope failed.
Message.UserResponse: Manually define the VariableMap SERVER_LOG_ROOT value as ${LOG_ROOT}/serverName under the server scope in the variables.xml file.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0460E=ADMG0460E: No property named {0} exists for node group {1}.
Message.Explanation: The specified property does not exist in the node group.
Message.UserResponse: Use the listNodeGroupProperties command to find available properties.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0807I=ADMG0807I: Property {0} is readonly. Will not be modified
Message.Explanation: Cannot modify property because the property is readonly.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0024W=ADMG0024W: Segment {1} of the containment path {0} is not correct.
Message.Explanation: The supplied parameter does not follow the detailed syntax described in the API documentation.
Message.UserResponse: Refer to the ConfigService#resolve method document for the syntax of a containment path.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0806I=ADMG0806I: Invalid Resource Id specified {0}.
Message.Explanation: The Resource Id is invalid.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0023W=ADMG0023W: Node creation is an invalid operation. Use the AddNode command-line utility instead.
Message.Explanation: The operation is not supported.
Message.UserResponse: Use the AddNode command-line utility to incorporate a node into a cell.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0805I=ADMG0805I: No object found for Resource Id {0} because it does not exist or user does not have required role. This object will not be removed.
Message.Explanation: The specified Resource Id object can not be removed because either the object does not exist or user does not have required role.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0022W=ADMG0022W: The system is unable to update the serverindex.xml document for server {0}: {1}.
Message.Explanation: The serverindex.xml document is not available for update. Some inconsistencies might exist between the serverindex.xml document and the rest of the configuration.
Message.UserResponse: Manually update the serverindex.xml document to keep it consistent with the configuration.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0493E=ADMG0493E: A node group with the name {0} already exists in the config.
Message.Explanation: The specified node group already exits in the configuration repository.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a different node group name and try the operation again.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0804I=ADMG0804I: No object found for Resource Id {0} and will not be created because create is disabled for this section.
Message.Explanation: The specified Resource Id object can not be created because create is disabled.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0492E=ADMG0492E: Un-Managed Node {0} can not be added to a node group.
Message.Explanation: The unmanaged node cannot be added to the node group because a node group must contain managed nodes only.
Message.UserResponse: Determine if the specified node is a managed node or if the correct node name was specified. Choose a managed node and retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0803I=ADMG0803I: No object found for Resource Id {0}. A new object will be created.
Message.Explanation: The specified Resource Id object is not found and a new object will be created.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0839I=ADMG0839I: Error found in this line {0}. Some or none of the properties were removed. Properties successfully removed {1}.
Message.Explanation: There is an error in the properties file at specified line number.
Message.UserResponse: Check the generated report file for details.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0021E=ADMG0021E: The system expected template type {0}, but the supplied template type is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The template type is different from the object type being created.
Message.UserResponse: Check the input parameters and verify that the template and object types match.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0491E=ADMG0491E: Node {0} is not eligible to be a member of node group {1}.
Message.Explanation: The specified node group is not a sysplex node group.
Message.UserResponse: Choose another node or node group and retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9229E=ADMG9229E: Neither the target object ID, nor the clusterName memberNode and memberName parameters, were specified to identify the cluster member.
Message.Explanation: A cluster member must be identified by specifying either a configuration object ID, or the names of the member, the node where the member resides, and the cluster to which the member belongs.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a cluster member object ID for the target object of the command, or by specify the valid names for the clusterName, memberNode, and memberName parameters of the command. Then retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0838I=ADMG0838I: Error found in this line {0}. Some or none of the properties were added. New value specified is {1}. Old value was {2}.
Message.Explanation: The section of properties was not applied due to error.
Message.UserResponse: Check the genereated report file for details about the error and fix the error in the properties file.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0802E=ADMG0802E: The user does not have sufficient privilege to modify object {0} in document {1}.
Message.Explanation: The user does not have privilege to modify an object in the document.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the user has sufficient privilege to modify the object in the document.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0020E=ADMG0020E: The required attribute {0} is not found.
Message.Explanation: A required attribute is not provided.
Message.UserResponse: Supply the required attribute.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0490E=ADMG0490E: Node {0} is not eligible to be a member of sysplex node group {1}.
Message.Explanation: The node is not eligible to be a member of the sysplex node group because Version 5 z/OS nodes can be a member of the default sysplex node group only.
Message.UserResponse: Do not attempt to add Version 5 nodes on the z/OS platform to a sysplex node group.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9228I=ADMG9228I: Cluster {0} deleted.
Message.Explanation: The specified cluster was successfully deleted from the configuration repository.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0837I=ADMG0837I: Removing property found on this line {0}. Properties successfully removed {1}.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0801E=ADMG0801E: The user does not have sufficient privilege to modify attribute {0} in document {1}.
Message.Explanation: The user does not have privilege to modify an attribute in the document.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the user has sufficient privilege to modify the attribute in the document.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0199W=ADMG0199W: Server {0} on node {1} cannot be found in any core group.
Message.Explanation: The system could not find the core group while performing a delete operation. The system continued the delete operation.
Message.UserResponse: Check the configuration to determine if a core group was inadvertently deleted.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9227E=ADMG9227E: Cannot find replication domain to delete for cluster {0}.
Message.Explanation: The replication domain for the specified cluster cannot be deleted because no replication domain having this cluster name can be found in the configuration repository.
Message.UserResponse: Verify the correct cluster name was specified, and that a replication domain exists for this cluster. If no replicaiton domain exists, specify a value of false for the deleteRepDomain parameter to skip the deletion of the replication domain.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0836I=ADMG0836I: A null value specified for property {0}. Old value for this property is {1}. Null value cannot be applied to the property. To remove property, use deleteConfigProperties command.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0800E=ADMG0800E: The user does not have sufficient privilege to modify document {0}.
Message.Explanation: The user does not have privilege to modify the document.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the user has the sufficient privilege to modify the document.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0198W=ADMG0198W: An exception occurred while trying to remove server {0} on node {1} from core group {2}: {3}.
Message.Explanation: While deleting the specified server, the system attempted to remove the server from its core group, but an exception occurred. The system continues the operation to delete the server.
Message.UserResponse: Evaluate the exception to determine the cause of the problem. Check the configuration to determine if a core group is inadvertently deleted.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9226E=ADMG9226E: A replicator entry with the member name {0} already exists.
Message.Explanation: A replicator entry cannot be created for the new cluster member because an existing replicator entry with the same name was already found in the replication domain.
Message.UserResponse: Verify whether the replicator entry exists for another cluster member. If it does, either choose another name for the new cluster member, or do not request the creation of a replicator entry for the cluster member.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0835I=ADMG0835I: Property {0} is readonly. The new value specified {1} is different from current value {2}. Readonly properties cannot be changed.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0197W=ADMG0197W: The system cannot find the parent node of server {0}.
Message.Explanation: The node cannot be found in the configuration on this server. The system continues the configuration operation.
Message.UserResponse: Check the configuration to determine if a node might be inadvertently deleted.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9225E=ADMG9225E: Cannot create replicator entry for member because no replication domain was found for cluster {0}.
Message.Explanation: A replicator entry cannot be created for the new cluster member because no replication domain can be found which has the name of the specified cluster.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that a replication domain has already been created for the cluster. If no replication domain has been created, create the replication domain and retry the operation. Alternatively, specify a value of false for the replicatorEntry parameter to skip the creation of a replication entry for the cluster member.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0834I=ADMG0834I: Property Name specified {0} is not known. Ignoring this property.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0196W=ADMG0196W: The system cannot find the {0} core group.
Message.Explanation: The specified core group cannot be found. The system continues with the configuration operation.
Message.UserResponse: Check the configuration to determine if the core group exists.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9224E=ADMG9224E: Cannot find the server for cluster member {0} on node {1} to use as template.
Message.Explanation: The server of the first cluster member, which is used as the template when creating additional cluster members, cannot be found.
Message.UserResponse: Verify the first cluster member has already been created and saved in the configuration repository. The first cluster member must be created before creating additional cluster members. Specify a template name, or template server and node, to create the first cluster member.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0833I=ADMG0833I: Syntax error found in this line {0}.
Message.Explanation: There is syntax error in the properties file at the specified line.
Message.UserResponse: Check generated report file for details and fix the syntax error.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0195W=ADMG0195W: Server {0} on node {1} cannot be added to core group {2}.
Message.Explanation: The system continues to create the new server. While creating the server, the server cannot be added to the specfied core group.
Message.UserResponse: Check the configuration to determine if the core group exists.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9223E=ADMG9223E: Cannot find server template {0}.
Message.Explanation: The specified template could not be found in the configuration repository.
Message.UserResponse: Verify the template name was specified correctly, the template exists, and the template is for a server type of configuration object. Specify a valid server template and retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0832I=ADMG0832I: Value specified for property {0} is out of range. Specified Value {1}. Required range {2}
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0614E=ADMG0614E: The specified short name {0} is invalid
Message.Explanation: The short name is invalid.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a different short name.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9222E=ADMG9222E: The firstMember command step and its parameters cannot be specified because one or more cluster members are already configured.
Message.Explanation: The firstMember command step can run only when the creating the first member of a cluster. When creating additional cluster members, the information specified in this step is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Check the cluster name and verify that you are creating the cluster member in the intended cluster. If you are, retry the operation without specifying the firstMember command step and any of its parameters.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0831I=ADMG0831I: Value specified for property {0} is not a valid type. Specified value {1}, Required type {2}
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0505E=ADMG0505E: Access Denied to access this config data {0}.
Message.Explanation: The current user does not have access to perform the intended operation on the specified configuration data.
Message.UserResponse: Login as a different user who has access to this config data.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9221E=ADMG9221E: The templateServerNode and templateServerName parameters must both be specified.
Message.Explanation: To use an existing server as a template to create the first member of a cluster, both the name and node of the server must be specified.
Message.UserResponse: Specify both the templateServerNode and templateServerName parameters, and retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0830I=ADMG0830I: Deleted property {0} in the configuration.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0504E=ADMG0504E: Cannot create server template using a server in a node {0} whose operating system is not known.
Message.Explanation: A server template cannot be created using a server on the specified node because the operating system is not specified for the node. The node might be a version 5 node in a mixed cell environment, and might not have been started.
Message.UserResponse: Start the node agent for the specified node. Ensure that the deployment manager is running. Then create the server template by using a server in the specified node.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9220E=ADMG9220E: The templateName parameter cannot be specified with either the templateServerNode and templateServerName parameters.
Message.Explanation: To create the first member of the cluster, a template name must be specified, or the name and node of an existing server to use as the template must be specified, but not both.
Message.UserResponse: Specify either the templateName paramater, or both the templateServerNode and templateServerName parameters, and retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0503E=ADMG0503E: Cannot create a new cluster member of version {0} on cluster which does not have any pre-existing cluster member of the same version.
Message.Explanation: The cluster member could not be created for the cluster because no cluster member exists at the product version specified for the new cluster member.
Message.UserResponse: Create a new cluster member at the same product version as an existing member of the cluster. For example, migrate one of the nodes of an existing cluster member to the same product version as the cluster member you are attempting to create for the cluster. The version of the cluster member changes when you migrate its node to the new version. Then create the new cluster member.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9255E=ADMG9255E: replicationDomain step is not valid for clusterType {0}
Message.Explanation: A replication domain can only be created for cluster type APPLICATION_SERVER.
Message.UserResponse: Change the clusterType parameter of the clusterConfig step, or remove the replicationDomain step.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0502E=ADMG0502E: A VariableMap object {1} already exists under scope {0}. There can be only one VariableMap object under a specific scope.
Message.Explanation: A VariableMap object already exists under the specified scope. Only one VariableMap object can exist under a specific scope.
Message.UserResponse: Do not attempt to create more than one VariableMap object per scope. Configure variables under just one VariableMap object for each scope.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9254E=ADMG9254E: The type of server, {0}, is not appropriate for the specified cluster type, {1}.
Message.Explanation: The type of server that is being converted to be the first member of the cluster must be appropriate for the type of cluster that is being created. Only proxy servers can be converted into a proxy server cluster and only application servers can be converted into an application server cluster.
Message.UserResponse: Change the clusterType parameter of the clusterConfig step, or change the server in the convertServer step to one of appropriate type.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0501E=ADMG0501E: Application scoped resource or variable configurations are not supported as application {0} contains one or more Version 5 deployment targets.
Message.Explanation: Application scope resource or variable configurations are introduced at Version 6.
Message.UserResponse: Configure the resource or variable at the server or node scope to achieve the same effect.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9253E=ADMG9253E: Cannot create new cluster member because, there is cluster member {0} with product version {1} on node {2}.
Message.Explanation: A new cluster member cannot be created because the specified cluster member already exists for the specified version and node.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the correct product version is installed on all the nodes and the deployment manager. You might need to updgrade the product installed on the node to a newer version. Consult the documentation to determine the supported configurations and operations for a cell that has nodes installed with different product versions.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0500E=ADMG0500E: Cluster scoped resource or variable configurations are not supported as cluster {0} contains one or more Version 5 members.
Message.Explanation: Cluster scope resource or variable configurations are introduced at Version 6.
Message.UserResponse: Configure the resource or variable at the server or node scope to achieve the same effect.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9252E=ADMG9252E: The firstMember command step must be specified because this member will be the first in the cluster.
Message.Explanation: The information specified in the firstMember command step is required when creating the first cluster member. The command step must be run.
Message.UserResponse: Check the cluster name and verify you are creating the cluster member in the intended cluster. If you are, retry the operation and specify the firstMember command step along with its required parameters.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9251E=ADMG9251E: Parameters are specified on command step {0} but the command step target is set to "false".
Message.Explanation: Because the value of the command step target is false, the step did not run. However, step parameters were specified, which indicate an intent to run the step.
Message.UserResponse: To run the command step, specify true for the command step target. If you do not want to run the command step, do not specify a command step target.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9250E=ADMG9250E: The {0} step of the {1} command did not validate for the following reason: {2}
Message.Explanation: The specified step of the specified command could not be validated.
Message.UserResponse: Evaluate the reason specified in the message to determine the problem. This is usually a problem with the command parameters. Correct the problem, and retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0459E=ADMG0459E: Node {0} cannot be removed from sysplex node group {1} because sysplex node group membership is required.
Message.Explanation: Nodes that belong to a sysplex node group must remain in a sysplex node group because sysplex node group membership is required.
Message.UserResponse: Use the addNodeGroupMember command to move a node to a different sysplex node group.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0458E=ADMG0458E: Custom property {0} already exists for node group {1}.
Message.Explanation: A node group property with the specified name already exists.
Message.UserResponse: Choose another name for the node group property, and try the operation again.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0421E=ADMG0421E: Node {0} is not eligible to be a member of node group {1}.
Message.Explanation: The specified node group is a sysplex node group in a different sysplex.
Message.UserResponse: Choose another node or node group and retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0457E=ADMG0457E: The default node group cannot be deleted.
Message.Explanation: The default node group cannot be deleted because a default node group is required for node group administration.
Message.UserResponse: Do not attempt to delete the default node group.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0420E=ADMG0420E: Node {0} is not eligible to be a member of node group {1}.
Message.Explanation: The specified node cannot be a member of the specified node group because the node group is a node group on the distributed platform.
Message.UserResponse: Choose another node or node group and retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0456E=ADMG0456E: Node group {0} cannot be removed because it contains members.
Message.Explanation: A node group cannot be removed if it contains members.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the node group members first and try the operation again.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0455E=ADMG0455E: Node {0} is not eligible to be a member of node group {1}.
Message.Explanation: The specified node is not eligible to be a member of the specified node group because the node group is a sysplex node group, which is unique to the z/OS operating system.
Message.UserResponse: Choose another node or node group and retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0454E=ADMG0454E: Node {0} is already a member of node group {1}.
Message.Explanation: The node member cannot be added to the node group because a member with that name already exists in the node group.
Message.UserResponse: Determine if the specified node is already in the node group, or if the correct node name is specified. Specify a valid node name and try the operation again.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0019E=ADMG0019E: The system is unable to locate the unique Java Message Service (JMS) server value on node {0}.
Message.Explanation: More than one JMS server value is defined on the specified node.
Message.UserResponse: Modify the configuration to remove the invalid JMS server value.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0453E=ADMG0453E: Cannot find node group {0} in the configuration repository.
Message.Explanation: The specified node group cannot be found in the configuration repository.
Message.UserResponse: Determine if the specified node group exists, and if the correct node group name is specified. Specify a valid node group name and try the operation again.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0489E=ADMG0489E: A sysplex node group with the short name {0} already exists.
Message.Explanation: The short name must be unique within the same sysplex.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the short name is unique within the same sysplex.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0018E=ADMG0018E: The system is unable to locate the node {0} for the WASQueue object {1}.
Message.Explanation: The node attribute value of the WASQueue instance is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Supply a valid node name as the attribute value for the node attribute on the WASQueue object.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0452E=ADMG0452E: Node {0} cannot be removed from node group {1}. This node must always be a member of at least one node group.
Message.Explanation: A node cannot be removed from a node group. A node must always be a member of at least one node group.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the node group contains at least one member.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0017E=ADMG0017E: The validate operation failed for session {0} and scope {1}.
Message.Explanation: The validate operation failed for the specified session and specified scope.
Message.UserResponse: See the nested exception for more details.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0451E=ADMG0451E: Node {0} cannot be removed from node group {1} because it is part of a cluster in that node group.
Message.Explanation: A node cannot be removed from a node group because it contains cluster members in that node group.
Message.UserResponse: Add the node that has cluster members to another node group before removing that node from the original node group.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0016E=ADMG0016E: The system is unable to get a validation manager for session {0}.
Message.Explanation: An exception occurred while obtaining a validation manager for the session.
Message.UserResponse: See the nested exception for information.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0015E=ADMG0015E: Attribute path {0} is read only and not modifiable.
Message.Explanation: The attribute path cannot be modified.
Message.UserResponse: Do not attempt to modify a read-only attribute path, or change attribute path permissions.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0014E=ADMG0014E: Attribute {0} is a read-only attribute.
Message.Explanation: You cannot modify the identified attribute.
Message.UserResponse: Do not attempt to modify a read-only attribute, or change attribute permissions.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0013E=ADMG0013E: The attribute value for attribute path {0} is not valid.

Message.Explanation: Invalid checkpoint type is specified in the command.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the delta checkpoint type is specified.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9239I=ADMG9239I: Cluster member {0} on node {1} deleted from cluster {2}.
Message.Explanation: The cluster member was deleted from the cluster.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9203E=ADMG9203E: Server {0} on node {1} is already a member of cluster {2}.
Message.Explanation: The server is already a member of the specified cluster. It cannot be a member of another cluster.
Message.UserResponse: Choose another server to include in the cluster, or do not include a server in the cluster. Then retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0812I=ADMG0812I: Not changing value for this property {0}. Reference to ObjectName which does not have display name is not supported.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0030E=ADMG0030E: The password for user ID {0} is not specified.
Message.Explanation: If a user ID is specified, a password must be specified when the defaultPrincipalMapping value is defined.
Message.UserResponse: Supply a password for the specified user ID.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0703E=ADMG0703E: Generic Exception during execution of command {0}
Message.Explanation: An exception is thrown during command execution.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the log file to determine the problem.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9202E=ADMG9202E: Cannot find server {0} on node {1}.
Message.Explanation: A server with the specified name is not configured on the specified node.
Message.UserResponse: Determine if the names of the server and node are correct. Specify the correct server and node names for a configured server. Then retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0811I=ADMG0811I: Changing value for this property {0}. New value specified is {1}. Old value was {2}.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9238E=ADMG9238E: Cannot find replicator entry for cluster member {0} in the replication domain for cluster {1}.
Message.Explanation: The replicator entry for the specified cluster member could not be found in the configuration repository.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the cluster member name and node are specified correctly, and that a replicator entry was created for the cluster member. If you are deleting a cluster member that has no replicator entry, specify a value of false for the deleteRepEntry parameter.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0702E=ADMG0702E: File name {1} specified for command {0} is invalid. It can not be created or it is not a file.
Message.Explanation: Invalid file name is specified in the command. The file can not be created or it is not a file.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the file name specified for the command is valid.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0629E=ADMG0629E: Server {0} on node {1} does not have template-metadata.xml
Message.Explanation: No template-metadata.xml is found in server or node.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the server or node has template-metadata.xml.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9201E=ADMG9201E: Replication domain already exists for cluster {0}.
Message.Explanation: A replication domain with the name of the specified cluster is already configured.
Message.UserResponse: If the named replication domain is no longer needed, delete it from the configuration. Otherwise, choose another name for the cluster. Then retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0810I=ADMG0810I: Not changing value for this property {0}. New value specified is same as current value {1}.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9237E=ADMG9237E: Cannot find replicator entry for cluster member {0} because no replication domain exists for cluster {1}.
Message.Explanation: The replicator entry for the specified cluster could not be found because there is no replication domain for the specified cluster.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that a replication domain exists for the specified cluster. A replicator entry cannot exist without a replication domain. If you are deleting a cluster member that has no replicator entry, specify a value of false for the deleteRepEntry parameter.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0701E=ADMG0701E: Checkpoint name {1} specified for command {0} is invalid. It does not exist.
Message.Explanation: Invalid checkpoint name is specified. The checkpoint name does not exist.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the checkpoint name specified for the command is valid.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0628E=ADMG0628E: Invalid feature pack or stack product name {1} specified for command {0}. Server does not contain the feature pack or stack product specified.
Message.Explanation: The feature pack or stack product name is invalid.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the feature pack or stack product name is valid.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0700W=ADMG0700W: As of {0}, the template {1} is deprecated and replaced by the template {2};
Message.Explanation: The template used has been deprecated, which still works, but some time in the future, it will no longer be available.
Message.UserResponse: Begin using the new template replacement as soon as possible.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9200E=ADMG9200E: Cluster {0} already exists.
Message.Explanation: A cluster with the specified name is already configured.
Message.UserResponse: Choose another name for the cluster, and retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9236E=ADMG9236E: Cannot find server for cluster member {0} on node {1}.
Message.Explanation: The server for the specified cluster member could not be found in the configuration repository.
Message.UserResponse: Verify the server was not deleted without removing the cluster member. Then retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0627E=ADMG0627E: Invalid feature pack or stack product name {1} specified for command {0}. Server already contains the feature pack or stack product specified.
Message.Explanation: The feature pack or stack product name is invalid.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the feature pack or stack product name is valid.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9235E=ADMG9235E: Cannot find cluster member {0} on node {1} in cluster {2}.
Message.Explanation: The specified cluster member could not be found in the configuration repository.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the cluster member name and node name are specified correctly, and that they represent an existing cluster member. Verify the member belongs to the specified cluster. If the member does not, specify the correct values and retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0844I=ADMG0844I: Endpoint {0} on server {3} does not exist and will be created with port {1} and host {2}.
Message.Explanation: The specified endpoint on the specific server does not exist and a new endpoint will be created.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0626E=ADMG0626E: Invalid feature pack or stack product name {1} specified for command {0}. Trying to add an already existing feature pack or stack product or trying to remove non-existant feature pack or stack product.
Message.Explanation: The feature pack or stack product name is invalid. The feature pack or stack product name must exist.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the feature pack or stack product name is valid.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9234E=ADMG9234E: The clusterName memberNode and memberName parameters were not all specified.
Message.Explanation: To identify a cluster member, the member name, node name and cluster name must all be specified.
Message.UserResponse: Specify the clusterName, memberNode, and memberName parameters. Retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0843I=ADMG0843I: Error modifying config object {0}. Check properties file for any invalid property value specified.
Message.Explanation: The object specified in the properties file section cannot be modified.
Message.UserResponse: Check the generated report file for details and fix the error in the properties file.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0625E=ADMG0625E: Invalid node name {1} and/or server name {2} specified for command {0}
Message.Explanation: The node name or server name is invalid.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the node name or server name is valid.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9233E=ADMG0233E: The clusterName memberNode and memberName parameters cannot be specified with the target object ID to identify the cluster member.
Message.Explanation: The cluster member can be identified either by specifying the member object ID, or by specifying the member name, node name and cluster name.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a cluster object ID for the command target object without specifying the clusterName, memberNode, and memberName parameters. Alternatively, specify all three of these parameters without specifying the target object ID.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0842I=ADMG0842I: Error deleting config object {0}. Check properties file to make sure object exists and not deleting any required or readonly property.
Message.Explanation: The object specified in the properties file section cannot be deleted.
Message.UserResponse: Check the generated properties file for details about the error and fix the error in the properties file.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0624E=ADMG0624E: Generic exception while executing command {0}
Message.Explanation: The generic exception occurred during the command execution.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the log file to determine the problem.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9232E=ADMG9232E: Cannot obtain the name of the cluster member's parent cluster.
Message.Explanation: The cluster name of the parent cluster could not be obtained for the cluster member during validation of the cluster member object ID.
Message.UserResponse: Verify the cluster member was not previously deleted. Then retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0841I=ADMG0841I: Error creating config object {0}. Check properties file for any missing properties that is required or invalid value specified for any property.
Message.Explanation: The object specified in the properties file section could not be created.
Message.UserResponse: Check the generated report file for details about the error and fix the error in the properties file.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0623E=ADMG0623E: Generic exception while validating parameters for command {0}
Message.Explanation: The generic exception occurred during the parameters validation.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the log file to determine the problem.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0659E=ADMG0659E: Generic Exception during execution of command {0}
Message.Explanation: An exception is thrown during command execution.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the log file to determine the problem.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9231E=ADMG9231E: Cannot find parent cluster of member {0} on node {1}.
Message.Explanation: The parent cluster object of the specified cluster member could not be found in the configuration repository.
Message.UserResponse: Verify the correct cluster member was specified, and the cluster itself was not previously deleted. Then retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0840I=ADMG0840I: Executing command {0}.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0622E=ADMG0622E: Invalid template name {1} specified for command {0}
Message.Explanation: The template name is invalid.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that a valid template name is specified.

Message.MsgText: ADMG0658E=ADMG0658E: Generic Exception during execution of command {0}
Message.Explanation: An exception is thrown during command execution.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the log file to determine the problem.

Message.MsgText: ADMG9230E=ADMG9230E: Cannot obtain the cluster member name and node name.
Message.Explanation: While validating the cluster member object ID, the member name and node could not be obtained.
Message.UserResponse: Verify the object ID is a valid ID for a cluster member, and not another type of configuration object. Then retry the operation.
